If you write Go code, you will realize you will actually not hit that problem often at all.<p>Right now the annoyance I hit more often is the inability to map a []Foo on an attribute .Name (string) to get a []string. I do that in ruby all the time, and with Golang it really sucks to do a for loop to collect stuff appending to a new array.<p><pre><code>  people.map(&:name) => [&quot;Joe&quot;, &quot;John&quot;]
</code></pre>
vs<p><pre><code>  a := make([]string, 0)
  for _, p := range people {
    a = append(a, p.Name)
  }</code></pre>
